title: Heinitz, Delich Sisters Advance to State
text:
Heinitz, Delich Sisters Advance to State 
By Zach Schneider Heinitz, Delich Sisters Advance to State October 20, 2015 Updated Oct 20, 2015 at 4:57 PM CDT 
Virginia, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Duluth Marshall seventh grader Nore Heinitz and the Eveleth-Gilbert sisters pairing of Cora Delich and Audrey Delich both won Section 7A girls' tennis titles on Tuesday afternoon and will advance to next week's MSHSL Class A tournament. 
Heinitz beat Pine City's Natalie Cahill 6-1, 6-1 to claim the singles title, dropping only four games in her six matches en route to the title. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
The pairing of Delich and Delich, meanwhile, beat Pequot Lakes' team of Sydney Holt and Haley Wiebolt 12 6-1, 6-4 to win the doubles title. 
Both Heinitz and the Delich sisters will begin play at the MSHSL Class A tournament on Oct. 29.
